try-of-defence","default_news_image":{"high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/63495d46d3bf7f618eda94d2/s960_ministry-of-defence-building.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/63495d468fa8f5346732690e/s300_ministry-of-defence-building.jpg"},"logo":{"crest":"mod","formatted_title":"Ministry<br/>of Defence"},"organisation_govuk_status":{"status":"live","updated_at":null,"url":null}},"document_type":"organisation","links":{},"locale":"en","schema_name":"organisation","title":"Ministry of Defence","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/ministry-of-defence","withdrawn":false}],"ordered_roles":[{"content_id":"84780b7b-c0f1-11e4-8223-005056011aef","details":{"body":"<p>The Queen’s Harbour Master and organisation exist to ensure safe and orderly passage and activity for all vessels within the waters of the Dockyard Port.</p>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Queen's Harbour Master\">QHM</abbr> is an independent authority accountable to the Secretary of State through Naval Base Commander who is primarily responsible for the protection of the port, the Royal Navy and its vessels and other government assets.However, they also have far wider responsibilities ranging from environmental issues, oil pollution contingency and response and conservation to the management of the water space for all users (military, commercial or leisure) and business continuity.</p>\n\n<p>This is achieved through:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a Dockyard Port Order</li>\n  <li>the provision of competent admiralty pilots and harbour controllers</li>\n  <li>liaison with other authorities with an interest in safe navigation in the port</li>\n</ul>\n\n","role_payment_type":null},"document_type":"board_member_role","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2014-11-21T14:54:31Z","schema_name":"role","title":"QHM Clyde","withdrawn":false},{"content_id":"84780c29-c0f1-11e4-8223-005056011aef","details":{"body":"<p>The Queen’s Harbour Master and organisation exist to ensure safe and orderly passage and activity for all vessels within the waters of the Dockyard Port.</p>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Queen's Harbour Master\">QHM</abbr> is an independent authority accountable to the Secretary of State through Naval Base Commander who is primarily responsible for the protection of the port, the Royal Navy and its vessels and other government assets.However, they also have far wider responsibilities ranging from environmental issues, oil pollution contingency and response and conservation to the management of the water space for all users (military, commercial or leisure) and business continuity.</p>\n\n<p>This is achieved through:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a Dockyard Port Order</li>\n  <li>the provision of competent Admiralty Pilots and Vessel Traffic Service Officers</li>\n  <li>liaison with other authorities with an interest in safe navigation in the port</li>\n</ul>\n\n","role_payment_type":null},"document_type":"board_member_role","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2014-11-25T15:54:14Z","schema_name":"role","title":"QHM Plymouth","withdrawn":false},{"content_id":"84780cd1-c0f1-11e4-8223-005056011aef","details":{"body":"<p>The Queen’s Harbour Master and organisation exist to ensure safe and orderly passage and activity for all vessels within the waters of the Dockyard Port.</p>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Queen's Harbour Master\">QHM</abbr> is an independent authority accountable to the Secretary of State through Naval Base Commander who is primarily responsible for the protection of the port, the Royal Navy and its vessels and other government assets.However, they also have far wider responsibilities ranging from environmental issues, oil pollution contingency and response and conservation to the management of the water space for all users (military, commercial or leisure) and business continuity.</p>\n\n<p>This is achieved through:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a Dockyard Port Order</li>\n  <li>the provision of competent admiralty pilots and harbour 